folder: Greenpoint Avenue & West Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Greenpoint Ave., west from West Street. In the foreground, is the City of New York Municipal Ferry to 23rd Street, Manhattan.

March 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: West St. & Greenpoint Ave., Brooklyn, NY
text:
West Street, north from Greenpoint Ave.
April 27, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

East River, pier, at the foot of Greenpoint Ave., showing the Municipal Ferry to 23rd Street, Manhattan. On the left partially seen is the American Export Lines pier. In the background are a group of buildings on the east side of West Street, between Java Street (left) and Greenpoint Ave. (right) belonging to Eherhard Faber Co., manufacturers of pencils.

April 27, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.
title: East River - Pier [American Export Lines] - Greenpoint Avenue, Brooklyn.
